about.summary: Split 'geospatial' objects into pieces. Includes support for some spatial object inputs, 'Well-Known Text', and 'GeoJSON'.
Split 'geospatial' objects into pieces. Includes support for some spatial object inputs, 'Well-Known Text', and 'GeoJSON'.

name: r-geoaxe
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '0.1.0' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-geoaxe
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/geoaxe_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/geoaxe/geoaxe_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 7ba4e5285670e67e307224222fcee5f7d6b67b6c1a5f7b8f34e64222d63c7e10

build:
  number: 4
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-jsonlite
    - r-rgeos
    - r-sp
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-jsonlite
    - r-rgeos
    - r-sp

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('geoaxe')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('geoaxe')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/ropenscilabs/geoaxe
  license: MIT
  summary: Split 'geospatial' objects into pieces. Includes support for some spatial object inputs,
    'Well-Known Text', and 'GeoJSON'.
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT'
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - jenzopr
